    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237634",
        "quote": "As the treaty made with the United States was the first treaty entered into by your country with other countries, therefore the President regards Japan with peculiar friendliness.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237634"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Country",
                "url": "/topics/country"
            },
            {
                "name": "United States",
                "url": "/topics/united_states"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237635",
        "quote": "The United States have no possessions in the east and do not desire to have any, as other countries do.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237635"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Possessions",
                "url": "/topics/possessions"
            },
            {
                "name": "United States",
                "url": "/topics/united_states"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237636",
        "quote": "Since the invention of steamships distant countries have become like those that are near at hand.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237636"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Like",
                "url": "/topics/like"
            },
            {
                "name": "Distant",
                "url": "/topics/distant"
            },
            {
                "name": "Countries",
                "url": "/topics/countries"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237640",
        "quote": "The nations of the West hope that by means of steam communication all the world will become as one family.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237640"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            },
            {
                "name": "All The World",
                "url": "/topics/all_the_world"
            },
            {
                "name": "Means",
                "url": "/topics/means"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237641",
        "quote": "Any nation that refuses to hold intercourse with other nations must expect to be excluded from this family.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237641"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Nation",
                "url": "/topics/nation"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            },
            {
                "name": "Intercourse",
                "url": "/topics/intercourse"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237642",
        "quote": "Two things are desired in order that intercourse may be had: First, that a minister or agent be allowed to reside at the capital. Second, that commerce between different countries be freely allowed.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237642"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "May",
                "url": "/topics/may"
            },
            {
                "name": "Agent",
                "url": "/topics/agent"
            },
            {
                "name": "Capital",
                "url": "/topics/capital"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237645",
        "quote": "Japan and China are isolated and without intercourse with other countries; hence the President directed me to attend to or watch the state of affairs in China also.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Townsend Harris",
            "url": "/quotes/townsend_harris_237645"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Other",
